==English==

{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
After the nationality of the [[logician]] [[w:Jan Łukasiewicz|Jan Łukasiewicz]]

===Noun===
'''[[Polish#Adjective|Polish]] [[notation]]'''

# {{cattag|arithmetic|logic}} A notation for [[arithmetic]] (and [[logical]]) [[formula]]e in which [[operation]]s (respectively, [[quantifier]]s and [[operand]]s) are written immediately before their [[operand]]s, used to avoid the need for [[parentheses]]; for example, 3 * (4 + 7) is written as * 3 + 4 7 and ''A'' [[AND]] ''B'' is written as '''AND''' ''A'' ''B''.

